Citations
Date: 0/0/1951
Source: NZ High Country
Author: MCLEOD
Vol / Page: 42
Edition:
Quote: I've heard a head shepherd say to a man "go down to the shed and put the red collar on those two dog tuckers in the yard." He meant the man to cut the throats of the sheep and skin them for the dogs.
